<HEADLINE>Student Loans gets new head</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>BARCLAY McBAIN Education Correspondent</BYLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>5</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974798864</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE Glasgow-based Student Loans Company has gone ``in-house'' for its new chief
executive.
Mr Colin Ward, the company's assistant managing director, saw off more than 200
external candidates for the job, replacing retiring acting chief executive Sir
Eric Ash.
Sir Eric, who will resume his earlier role as non-executive director, was
appointed when the company's fortunes were at their lowest.
Thousands of students were left penniless after a new system to deal with
repeat borrowers failed. Universities were also angered by the company's
failure to handle the many urgent inquiries.
Sir Eric took over from the company's first chief executive, Mr Ron Harrison,
who was sacked for alleged financial irregularities.
Mr Ward, a chartered accountant, joined the company in 1990.
</TEXT>
