<TEXT>
Former Middle East hostage John McCarthy and pupils from a London school took
part yesterday in a protest outside the Commons against the
Immigration and Asylum Bill. Tanzeela Khan, 13, left, from Pakistan, and
Feyrus
Hussain, from Somalia, were two of the pupils from George Mitchell School,
Waltham Forest, who performed a 10-minute play about a young Kurdish boy
forced
to flee his homeland.
