<DATE>951220</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Jury fails to reach verdict</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974798919</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
--Jurors in the case of Gordon Wardell, accused of murdering his wife, were
sent to a hotel last night after failing to reach a verdict.
Wardell, 42, of Meriden, Warwickshire, denies murdering Woolwich building
society boss Carol, 39, in September last year.
</TEXT>
