<HEADLINE>Stately world of a swindler</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974799079</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE centre of Lord Brocket's world is the 25-bedroom Georgian stately home set
in 1400 acres that provides his income and houses his fabulous #20m car
collection.
The 3rd Baron Brocket inherited Brocket Hall in Hertfordshire, once the home of
Lady Caroline Lamb, in 1965 at age 13.
In 1981, he opened it as a premier international conference centre.
Lord Brocket's widely-publicised marriage to American heiress Isabell Lorenzo,
34, ended in divorce in September.
</TEXT>
